snippet.textDisplay:
BECAUSE of the way the Australian authorities treat Novak Djokovic, there have been rumors that Australia could lose the organization of one of the four-year Grand Slam!
That is not excluded, believes the co-president of the International Association of Tennis Journalists, the British Simon Cambers.

"There is a small possibility, but is not impossible," Cambers said.

Although he emphasized that it is too early to think about that possibility "despite a lot of criticism, not only because of how everything was conducted around Novak, but also because of the way Tennis Australia communicates", it is clear that this is one of the possibilities.

The reason why Cambers sees that Australia could keep the organization of the Grand Slam is that it has invested a lot in this tournament, especially in the last twenty years.

- The players love this tournament, but there have been threats in recent years that the tournament could be moved somewhere in the Asia-Pacific zone. There are other countries that would like to organize a Grand Slam - says the co-president of International Association of Tennis Journalists and states that such a change would require a change in the already complicated calendar.

There were a lot of comments on that topic on social networks as well. Among other things, some participants believe that the tournament may in the future be moved to a country where the rules are less powerful, in favor of the tennis game, so that there will not be new complications like the ones Novak Djokovic encountered.

Everything that happened to him can happen to us tomorrow.

Support and love for Novak Djokovic, support for freedom of choice and speech!
